page.title: 09LIVING IN WEST WITTERING
page.content: I live in West Wittering.It is the most South Westerly point in West Sussex.I like living in West Wittering because my hous is by the sea.My dad runs a car park which is used by visitors to the beach.Sometimes during the height of the season the queue of cars waiting to enter the car park stretches way along the main road to Chichester.The highest number of cars we had on one occasion in the car park was four thousand vehicles.I go to West Wittering School in Pound Road. The new school was opened by the Duchess of Norfolk in 1981.It was a great occasion for the village.We had a special church service.In the village there is an old church,a nursing home,several shops,a service station,a restruant,a public house and an old sheep wash.
